      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''The Spoils of Defeat'' (editorial, Nov. 24), you say ''G.O.P. leaders are preparing to walk away from their most basic constitutional responsibility -- passing a budget.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In ''The Spoils of Defeat'' (editorial, Nov. 24), you say ''G.O.P. leaders are preparing to walk away from their most basic constitutional responsibility -- passing a budget.''</p>
        <p>The Republican leaders are stubbornly opposed to a cut-and-run strategy for solving Iraq's problems.</p>
        <p>Paradoxically, they appear quite eager to implement that same strategy when it comes to addressing the needs of this nation.</p>
        <p>Barry Sachais  West Milford, N.J., Nov. 24, 2006</p>
      </block>
